<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lower2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lower</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Lour,</orth> vb. to frown, to look sullen: <bibl n="shak. ven 75" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 75" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 75</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.187" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 6</bibl>. With <emph>on</emph> or <emph>upon,</emph> to mark the object: <bibl n="shak. son 149.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 149, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.283" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 94</bibl>. With <emph>at,</emph> to mark the cause: <cit><quote>why at our justice seemest thou then to l.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.235" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 235</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>